parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Driver's Side Door Panel)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system in the driver's side door panel can cause a fire, smoke, and electrical smell, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Flame or smoke emanating from the driver's side door panel
electrical smell
malfunctioning windows and door controls
intermittent false fuel readings
and uncontrolled window movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Window and Door Lock Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power windows and door locks can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and safety risks, especially if the windows or doors become stuck in an open or closed position.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete failure of power windows and door locks
slow or uncontrolled window movement
and inability to open or close windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can lead to continued safety risks and inconvenience for vehicle owners, as they may experience electrical system failures, fires, or other issues.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but lack of available parts or repair scheduling
leading to prolonged wait times for repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel gauge can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, causing drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, stranding, or engine damage.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect readings
such as indicating an empty tank when it's full or vice versa
fluctuating between full and empty
or stuck on a specific reading. The low fuel warning light may come on prematurely or not at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: One or both headlights randomly turn off while driving
sometimes coming back on after turning the lights off and back on; low beams flash on and off while driving; headlights fail to work altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Controlled Air Suspension System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic controlled air suspension system can cause the vehicle to sag or lean to one side, affecting its stability and handling, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The rear portion of the vehicle fails to raise
the air suspension compressor and/or air bags fail to engage consistently
the system leaks
the vehicle sags or leans to one side
difficulty driving
especially in cold temperatures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system to calibrate correctly can cause the vehicle to sag or lean to one side, affecting its stability and handling, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The system fails to calibrate correctly
the vehicle sags or leans to one side
difficulty driving
especially in cold temperatures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side mirror control can cause visibility issues, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The side mirror control does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The grinding noise while turning can cause wear and tear on the vehicle's components, leading to premature failure and potential accidents.
symptoms: Grinding noise while turning right.
